cs.DC, cs.NI, cs.SE, cs.SY, cs.CE

The paper discusses resource management in cloud computing systems, which involves distributed computing and networking. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also discusses Service Level Agreement (SLA)-oriented resource allocation, which involves network protocols and communication. Therefore, cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also a likely category. The paper also discusses architectural elements and autonomic resource management, which are related to software engineering and systems. Therefore, cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) are also likely categories. Finally, the paper discusses market-based resource management, which involves economics and game theory. Therefore, cs.CE (Computational Economics and Finance) is a less likely but still possible category.
